<subSubSection id="C353652ADB28D86CFF7112F9FCA64B8C" pageId="6" pageNumber="69" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BF636A1DB28D86CFF7112F9FCA64B8C" blockId="6.[151,1436,896,1066]" pageId="6" pageNumber="69">
This species is probably allied to 
<taxonomicName id="4C494D22DB28D86CFDEE12F8FDEF4BF5" authorityName="Ohara &amp; Hayashi" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Dworakowska" baseAuthorityYear="1993" box="[520,588,897,922]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Igutettix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ater">
<emphasis id="B93DEAB3DB28D86CFDEE12F8FDEF4BF5" box="[520,588,897,922]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="69">I. ater</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but is distinguishable by the male genital characters: aedeagal shaft bearing angulate extensions dorso-basally and smooth latero-vetral sides, and having ventral process curved at apical ⅓. Body length: 
<specimenCount id="9D4FFD28DB28D86CFED612B0FEE64B8C" box="[304,325,969,995]" pageId="6" pageNumber="69" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
<specimenCount id="9D4FFD28DB28D86CFEAA12B0FEC24B8C" box="[332,353,969,995]" pageId="6" pageNumber="69" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
<quantity id="4CB19B44DB28D86CFE8E12B1FE4C4B8C" box="[360,495,968,995]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.65" metricValueMax="4.7" metricValueMin="4.6" pageId="6" pageNumber="69" unit="mm" value="4.65" valueMax="4.7" valueMin="4.6">4.6–4.7 mm</quantity>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFD84B50DB28D86CFE1B12B1FD5A4B8C" author="Dworakowska, I." box="[509,761,968,995]" pageId="6" pageNumber="69" pagination="97 - 139" refId="ref6637" refString="Dworakowska, I. (1993 b) Fusiplata Ahmed and some other Dikraneurini (Insects, Auchenorrhyncha, Cicadellidae: Typhlocybinae). Entomologische Abhandlungen Staatliches Museum fur Tierkunde Dresden, 55 (7), 97 - 139." type="journal article" year="1993">Dworakowska, 1993b</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
